messages.content: So the issue is that you can't find your friends through the search?
do we have an answer?

You have to specify your character key in the character setting
If you add a key then you will always apply as key holder (you can set which levels exactly), and if you don't then you will apply without a key

if the name of said friend is too common, it won't appear on that list (I believe that list is only meant to show the either the 5 more active or the first 5 that used the website), a solution for this would be a different search bar that only allows you to search with their exact discord tag (discord tags are unique as opposed to discord nicknames)

it'll also be awesome if we could add the current group members to the friend list (currently the 3 options are kick, promote as a leader, and leave the group)
this last line is specifically for the scenario of "I want to add the friend of my friend that joined our group, but I can't find him on the search bar"

it'll also be helpful if we can add a "no key" option inside of the key select section, currently we need to exclude and include the character for it to appear as a non key holder

that and the possibility to order your characters inside of the list (making it either high IO will get the first spot of the column/row, or excluded characters will appear at the bottom of the list)
